        <fr:title text="Ordering material">Ordering material</fr:title>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <html:p>The choice to order material partially reflects how I learned it (<fr:link href="/ela/" title="Elementary linear algebra" uri="http://localhost:8000/ela/" display-uri="ela" type="local">Elementary linear algebra</fr:link>, followed by intermediate linear algebra, then <fr:link href="/ca/" title="Classical Analysis" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca/" display-uri="ca" type="local">Classical Analysis</fr:link>, and so on) and partially how I mentally think of the material: linear algebra is the "central" subject in Mathematics, and everything "branches off" from it.</html:p>
        <html:p>This means we successively review linear algebra in greater generality.</html:p>
        <html:p>Moreover, I have decided to "cluster" trees into "subforests" reflecting the course materials. This means each "identifier" for a tree is prefixed by some "slug" for the "subforest". Sometimes (like with <html:code>field</html:code> or <html:code>sl</html:code>) a mathematical object or gadget is used as the slug. Othertimes (like with <html:code>ela</html:code> or <html:code>ca</html:code>) the course name is used.</html:p>
        <html:p>I'll typically try to follow the <fr:link href="https://arxiv.org/archive/math" type="external">categories used by arXiv</fr:link>.</html:p>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
